description: 1972 Mercedes Benz 350SL, A rare car and this particular one was the 376th produced for this new 107 Body style. I have taken many photos of this car, it is a California car no rust issues, and currently has 149,000 miles. Clean California title.

Finished in bright red nonmetallic the paint has excellent depth and shine, very straight with no damage, alignment of the doors, windows, top, as well as the hood and trunk all align nice. This car has had a professional respray some years ago, the factory paint has shown its age. The Hard top is in excellent shape as well as the headliner, there is a dark brown soft top also in good condition. The Centra chrome wheels are peeling, tires have some age to them. Chrome in good condition as well as rubber bumper inlays.

Interior is black, very tidy and well kept, very small crack on dash near vent for defrost, and all gauges, lights horn etc. are working. Factory AC car that does blow but will need a charge of Freon, power windows, upgraded stereo, Clifford kill switch. Carpet is good with wear to the driver side floor pillar as seen in the photo.
This 4.5 Litre motor runs very well, no smoke, strange noises, fluids are all clean and up to date, transmission shifts well and brakes also work well, there is a little play in the steering wheel.
All factory books, including the metal warranty card. Shipping assistance available, these are getting harder find in this condition and are on upswing in the collector car market…

description: 1986 Mercedes Benz 560SL (2 Top Convertible) R107 BodyStyle

description: This very collectable 1972 Mercedes-Benz 350SL R107 Roadster with only 78,063 original/documented miles was the first year of the US model 107 series.  Off White (717) with Black (040) hardtop, new black German canvas soft top, and immaculate Black (161) MB Tex interior.  This vehicle has been a single family owned vehicle since the early 1980s and comes with all original books and records.  The former owner left the vehicle to his son and daughter with all documentation.  Loaded with features including:  4.5L V8 engine, steel block and small European-style bumpers, 3-speed automatic transmission, new battery, cold air conditioning, original Becker German Europa audio system, original tool kit, power steering, power brakes, power antenna, steel wheels with classic hubcaps on recent 305/70R14 thin white wall tires, and much more. In addition it has had a fresh service in our own shop.  All mechanicals are factory original and in great working order.  the paint work and chrome is in excellent condition with all panels and doors fitting perfectly.  This is one of the nicest we have owned in 30 years.  This extremely cl ean and original classic convertible is perfect to drive or show.  The R107 model came on the scene in 1972 as a replace to the W113 series and had minimal changes until 1989 as a testament to its popularity.  It consisted of the debut of the V8 engine on the convertible weight.  Interestingly they were dubbed originally as 350SL despite having a 4.5L V8 engine to keep with the model designation for Europe.  A true classic vehicle.  View more pictures and information at www.europeanmotorcars-ltd.com
